<TITLE> Govt might allow older car imports </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 9 (bdnews24.com)  The government is considering to increase the age limit of imported automobiles said the commerce minister on Sunday. Commerce minister Faruk Khan said that the government might increase the current bar on importing vehicles more than five years old to eight years. It is being considered because five year old reconditioned vehicles are not very available in Japan. The measure would apply to durable and modern reconditioned buses and other vehicles. A statement on Sunday revealed this information. It said that the commerce minister said this at programme inaugurating the office of Bangladesh Reconditioned Vehicles Importers and Dealers Association (BARVIDA) on the 13th floor of Akram Tower at 15/5 Bijoynagar. The programme was attended by Japanese ambassador Tamotsu Shinotsuka, FBCCI president Anisul Haque and others
